name: Aston Denpasar Hotel & Convention Center

review 1: Nice hotel, friendly staff from security, bell boy, front officer and f&b staff. The Indonesia menu as breakfast is tasty, you must try their black coffee. Nice to stay here, our room was upgraded üëç
review 2:
The room is spacious and clean. This is an old hotel, so please tolerate a bit of tear and wear. The receptionist who served me (for check in) was slow and not friendly (not even a smile), but the housekeeper and waiters are friendly and helpful.
I was here for a meeting and stayed for a couple of nights. The hotel is located on a very busy street so watch yourself when trying to cross the road. A bit of a drive from the airport and the traffic is horrible.
review 3:
A 4 star hotel but doesn't feel like it. Old furniture, some of them need to be renewed. Guest can't open their windows for some weird reason or rules.

We asked front desk 2 times (via telephone call) for an extra bed and they told us to wait for them to inform us, but they didn't contact us at all for both requests.

It's not the best option for vacation, it's more suitable for a business trip because of the strategic location in the city.

name: Sambal Bakar Indonesia

review 1:
The food is delicious, ü§§

review 1: Bad quality equipment, you need to change this for real. Cuz today i just dropped my pink lava , the tray really bad ,it makes the drink not stable when i carried it. Also the chashier didnt help me for this, they just stay quite and didnt help me at all.

Parking lot is not much for car, better to use motorbike / gofood to order the food.

I dont know about others but their lava drinks is not for me.
review 3: Fried chicken with different sauces, if you are a foreigner you should know that this restaurant chain don‚Äôt have spoons or forks. You have to eat with hands ( mean fingers ) .... but it‚Äôs a good experience here. Nice and clean place with chill ac and free wifi.

review 5: Finally tried this popular Chicken and cheese combo. I really loved the chicken, the spiciness qas amazingly delicious! Although I'm not really a fan dipping it to the cheese sauce. Just the spicy chicken coated with BBQ sauce already great. Probably what needs to be improved greatky was their choice of drinks. Both the Taro and Strawberry drinks weren't that good. Their dessert, the cake in cup was amazing tho. I tried the Pandan one, and it tasted wonderful!!!

name: NOLDA POCHA DENPASAR
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.315, Pemecutan Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1:
I've been here several times but only now had the chance to write a review. The place is easy to find, but parking is limited, especially if you bring a car.

There are many Korean food options that suit the Indonesian palate, but there's no bibimbap or gimbap here.

The staff used to be stern and unfriendly, but after a few visits, they inexplicably became friendlier. I hope this attitude is maintained.

The food is tasty, although sometimes the portions are generous, and other times a bit small.
review 2:
There's package for two, below 200K. Which is great compared to other Korea BBQ.

Love the Boricha! Tea with slight grilled taste, only 15K and got one big jug of iced tea.

Taste all decent. We enjoyed our visit there.

Venue a bit "run down" But not a big problem.
review 3: Good place to eat korean food. Fordable and tasty. Recommended place to eat in Denpasar! üòäüëç
review 4: Potato chese bread is my favourite! It has plenty of mozzarella cheese and taste so good! The chicken feet is tasty but when u cook, the oil is spalshing everywhere. Overall the food is okay but in my experience the service was not good. The waitress kind of absent mindedly and not answering our question about the food properly.
review 5: Love the food and vibes! Also the place, it looks like in Korean drama! Plus, they play BLACKPINK‚Äôs song when I eat there. 5 stars!

name: OYO 91498 Hotel Diana
address: Ubung, Denpasar Utara, Denpasar City, Bali 80116, Indonesia
review 1: The hotel was not very large, it had two floors and enough space to accommodate several cars. I got a busted ac facility and a busted toilet. There were two beds, no blankets and no pillows. I think the facility could be improved even better.
review 2:
we were staying 4 days; room and beds are okay the bathroom might thow some off, you shover with a bucket and flush with a little bucket/ a hose. There are spiderwebs and the walls ate dirty; overall not that clean but very cheap to stay here..
We had (pre paid) reservations at diana 2 but they said as we arrived that they were fully booked! Communication is really bad..without google translate not really doable at diana 1&2 the same (just to know). However the people at diana 1 were really nice actually (diana 2 not at all)! Big problem was that we could barely sleep, in the "community/sitting area" wich is the middel of the hotel were people from the staff talkin until late at night or watching some showa on tv; rooms have zero isolation you hear everything. If you want to have good sleep book somewhere else..
The location is good, but you should rent a scooter
review 3: Another one of those that tell you "no room" after you arrive even if you book via official site AND prepay... freaking unbelievable. Do NOT book here and if for some crazy reason you do, get here very early in the day so you can confirm if they actually have room. Email confirmation means nothing, as I found out. He told me to ask for refund with Oyo....
review 4: Is not even oyo anymore.. got scam by oyo nevet trust oyo for apps booking.... when I arrived at the olace is not even oyo anymore.....

i can say it is a hidden gem because it is located behind the Informa store. compared to its services and price, it is classified as a worthy place to stay for some nights.
the places are clean. the rooms are big and clean. there's a TV but I don't think it can be used tho (who watches TV these days?). the bedroom also has an AC which is working fine. the toilet is clean and wide, but I have a problem accessing its hot water. it is working fine, but I find it hard to find the right composition for hot water.
the place has a relatively clean swimming pool. but when I came there, its water is kinda dirty which is caused by falling flowers (but ok).

address: Jl. Pidada IV No.15, Ubung, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1:
Find traditional Javanese beef stew fishes here! If you are craving sweet, savoury and hot beef broth this place is the one.

Located in Denpasar Utara area, you will find the place hidden in the corner of a bumpy road.

The food was amazing, their service and higyene of the place can be improved a lot though.
review 2: Javanese style beef rib soup and rice in coconut milk. Quite ok. It is a traditional warung, so place could be very crowded and hot.
